@graph.label: Place
@graph.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

@graph.label: RecommendedDeduplication
@graph.description: A record indicating a suggestion that two entities should be deduplicated.

@graph.label: Trigger to Verb Mapping
@graph.description: A type of SKL Mapping that specifies what should be done when a Trigger from a particular integration is received.

@graph.label: Dataview
@graph.description: A stored view on data in a Standard Storage.

@graph.label: context
@graph.description: A JSON-LD Context Definition used to compact entities into a more human readable format

@graph.label: parameterMapping
@graph.description: An RML TriplesMap specifying how the standard parameters of a Verb or Trigger should be translated into the unique parameters of a targeted Verb or Integration operation.

@graph.label: parameterMappingFrame
@graph.description: A JSON-LD Frame used to transform the JSON-LD returned by a parameterMapping into the format required by the targeted Verb or Integration operation.

@graph.label: operationMapping
@graph.description: An RML TriplesMap specifying how the parameters of the Verb should be used to determine the name and type of the operation to perform in the Integration.

@graph.label: verMapping
@graph.description: An RML TriplesMap specifying what target Verb should be executed depending on the parameters supplied to an original Verb or Trigger.

@graph.label: verbId
@graph.description: A literal value to be used as a shortcut for the id of the target Verb to execute instead of the skl:verbId predicate of the skl:verbMapping.

@graph.label: returnValueMapping
@graph.description: An RML TriplesMap specifying how the unique return value of the Integration should be translated into the standard return value of the Verb. In the case of a VernNounMapping, this specifies how the parameters of the Verb should be directly translated into a return value..

@graph.label: returnValueFrame
@graph.description: A JSON-LD Frame used to transform the JSON-LD returned by the `returnValueMapping` into a prefered format. This field overrides the returnValueFrame of the Verb. If not supplied, the Verb's returnValueFrame will be used instead.
